# Normalize line endings to LF in the repo and on checkout.
#
# This guarantees that `ruff format --check` passes on Windows even when the
# user has `git config --global core.autocrlf true`. Ruff's `line-ending = "lf"`
# setting (see pyproject.toml) means Ruff writes LF; if Git checks out CRLF,
# every file shows up as "would reformat".
#
# With `text=auto eol=lf`, Git stores LF in the repo and checks out LF on
# every platform, regardless of the user's autocrlf setting.
#
# PowerShell scripts (.ps1) traditionally want CRLF on Windows, but PowerShell
# 5.1+ and PowerShell Core 6+ both handle LF fine, so we normalize them too
# for consistency. This matches Microsoft's own repos (e.g. PowerShell/PowerShell).
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary files - never normalize.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.pdf binary
*.zip binary
*.gz binary
*.sqlite binary
*.db binary
